<HEAD>
<TITLE> Whatsnew</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" text="000044" link="0000ff" vlink="660099">




<A HREF="index.html">
<img src="home_btn.gif" 
     hspace=5
     align="middle" 
     alt="HOME">

VILLAGE Home Page
</A>

<p>
<img src="/icons/line_sun.gif" alt="----------">
<p>

<h2>WHAT&#39;S NEW IN THE VILLAGE</h2><p><ul>
<p><ul>

<LI>The Internet course on<A HREF="events.html"><B> risk behavior</B></A> being offered through the Safety Center at St Cloud University in Minnesota is on track. The syllabus is ready, enrollments have begun and the Web pages through which the course will be conducted are in the process of preparation. Further announcements will be made in February.<P>

<LI><A HREF="events.html"><B> Coming events</B></A> has been updated with information about the American Driver and Traffic Safety Education Association conference (Minnesota, Aug.) and the Vision in Vehicles conference (France, Sept.). Also, parts of the Fall issue of  ADTSEA's <A HREF="resource.html"><B>The Chronicle </A> </B> are now available in the Resource section. More will follow. <P>

<LI><B>A NEW WEBSITE,</B><A HREF="http://www.drivers.com/pol/"><B> Performance-On-Line</B></A>, has been added to the <A HREF="homepage.html"><B>The Village Community</A>. </B> Performance-On-Line is a computerized driving test that measures cognitive skills which are critical to complex activities such as driving a motor vehicle or piloting an aircraft. The test was developed over 10 years of basic research in cooperation with labs all over the world.<P>

<LI><A HREF="events.html"><B>A new entry</B></A> has been added to <B>Coming Events</B> - a Call for Papers for the <B>Traffic Safety on Two Continents</B> conference which will be held in Lisbon, Portugal on September 22- 24, 1997. Coming Events has just been updated for 1997. Please send us details of any traffic safety/traffic education-related events for inclusion.<P>

<LI><A HREF="peace/"><B>Peace of Mind Sign</B></A> A new Home Page has been added to the Village community. It is of special interest to parents or anyone with an interest in helping parents provide effective practice. <P>

<LI><A HREF="ARTICLES/restricted/fulnews-952033853.html"><B>Driver/<B>Education</B> FALL ISSUE. Vol. 6 # 4</B></A> Now available to subscribers in the Resources area of the Village<P>

<LI><A HREF="ARTICLES/restricted/oneill-96342-15393.html"><B>Interview with Brian O'Neill</B></A> For the past decade or more, the driver education community have complained that the Insurance Institute For Highway Safety has been negative towards driver training and education. In the interview with IIHS president Brian O'Neill reported here, Dr. O'Neill  answers some pointed questions that indicate his position on driver training and education, and his views about the recent initiative to form a coalition of sponsors to help fund development projects in driver education. <P>

<LI><B>Coming soon</B></A> The latest issue of <i>Driver/<B>Education</B></i> and recent issues of the ADTSEA <i>Chronicle</i> will be available soon.<P>


<LI><A HREF="highway.html"><B>Leon James Traffic Psychology</B></A> page. The link to this page has now been updated and it can, once again, be reached through the Village Guide to the Highway. Dr James is Professor of Psychology at the University of Hawaii. The Web site contains principles of Traffic Psychology, definitions, methodologies, student projects. <P>

<LI><A HREF="ARTICLES/news/larson-96301-13300.html"><B>Changing attitudes towards aggressive driving</B></A> - An article by Dr. John A. Larson MD has been added to the Village news area. His work at the Yale medial school and the Institute of Stress Medicine is discussed. Also his new book. He offers an attitude-change method that is backed by research.<P>

<LI><B>Alcohol Education for New Drivers</B> -  In 1995, the Toronto-based Addiction Research Foundation (Toronto), in collaboration with the  Ontario Road Safety Educators Association and the Driving School Association of Ontario, conducted a needs assessment survey of driver educators
across the Province. An executive summary of the results is now available for <A HREF="ARTICLES/restricted/ARFalcohol-96298-11048.html">Village subscribers</A> under Training and Education in the Village Library<P>

<LI><B>A "virtual classroom" </B> seminar on Risk Homeostasis Theory and its implications for risk-taking behavior will be conducted early in the new year by Minnesota's St. Cloud State University. See <A HREF="events.html">coming events</A> for details. <P>

<LI>Basic and Advanced ,<B>Accident Investigation School,</B> Jan/Feb '96 and February 24-March 7, 1997.  See <A HREF="events.html">coming events</A> for details. <P>

<LI><B>Learning to drive in Russia - </B>Finnish traffic safety researcher Reima Lehtimaki and anthropologist Aune Kamarainen visited the Russion republic of Mari El (about 600 km east of Moscow) earlier this year. They have provided for the village a unique insight into the administration of driver licensing, driver training and education in this region. Read the <A HREF="ARTICLES/news/mariel-96297-10171.html">article</A> in the news section. A much longer report is available in the General section of the <A HREF="ARTICLES/restricted/Russia-96297-9836.html">library</A> for Village subscribers.  <P>


<LI><B>New to the Road. Reducing the Risks for Young Motorists. </B>The proceedings of a major international conference on driver licensing, training and education have recently been released. Organized by the Youth Enhancement Service, a part of the Brain Information Service of the University of California at Los Angeles, and the Traffic Injury Research Foundation of Canada, the publication has 148 pages with papers from an international  panel of traffic safety experts. <A HREF="ARTICLES/restricted/newto-96297-10178.html">details</A>. are available to subscribers.<P>

<LI>Now available exclusively at the Village bookstore - <B>The Dangerous Edge: The psychology of excitement</B> by Michael J. Apter. Professor Apter explores the reasons why people seek out risk and excitement and under what conditions. He offers us ways to manage our "protective frame" so that we can recognize what is genuinely threatening or risky and to control the risks we take so as to have more excitement and fun without courting disaster.  <A HREF="books.html">Bookstore</A>.
<P>
<LI><strong><A HREF="/cgi-bin/PDE/pde-getnews.pl?keyword=summit-96288-5239">Read about a remarkable &quot;summit&quot; meeting</A></strong> which took place in Washington D.C. on September 16 and 17. The meeting was remarkable for at least two reasons--it was the first major initiative aimed at improving driver performance in almost two decades; and, most remarkable of all,  it had the unique goal of bringing together a Gulf-War-style alliance of <strong>powerful private, public and non-profit partners</strong> in an all-out struggle against a common enemy, the casualty toll on our roads. <strong><A HREF="/cgi-bin/PDE/pde-getnews.pl?keyword=summit-96269-1488">Read an article</A></strong> about the summit by participant David Thompson. Subscribers may obtain more information about the <strong><A HREF="/ARTICLES/restricted/partic.html">summit participants</A></strong>. 
<P>

<LI>The Licensing, Testing and Development division of the Drivers License Department of the <STRONG>Swedish National Road Administration</STRONG> has joined the Village community. <A HREF="swedish.html">Check out their Home Page</A>.
<P>


<p>


</BODY>



