<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<TD><STRONG>August 2 - 7, 1997</STRONG>
<BR>St. Cloud, Minnesota</TD>
<TD><STRONG>AMERICAN DRIVER AND TRAFFIC SAFETY EDUCATION ASSOCIATION ANNUAL CONFERENCE</STRONG><br>
 The agenda for this year's conference is still in the process of development. In the meantime, ADTSEA's conferences are always warm and hospitable events and the host committee are putting together a program to make this a memorable event. St. Cloud is on the Missippi River about 50 miles NE of Minneapolis. In the land of Lake Woebegone, golf and tennis are major attractions (St. Cloud has been called "Tennistown USA"). Discount airfares have been arranged and a free shuttle to the hotel (Holiday Inn) is available. Updates will be posted in this space when available.<br>
For more information call Tel: 320-255-3023. Fax: 320-255-4237. 

</TD></TR><P>

<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<TD><STRONG>September 14 - 17, 1997</STRONG>
<BR>Marseilles, France</TD>
<TD><STRONG>SEVENTH INTERNATIONAL 'VISION IN VEHICLES' CONFERENCE</STRONG><br>
 The Vision in Vehicles will be run in conjunction with the Applied Vision Association, the Ergonomics Society and the Association of Optometrists with the participation of INRETS (Institut National de Recherche sur les Transports et leur Securite). This multi-disciplinary conference will provide an international forum for the exchange of information on current research encompassing all aspects of vision and its relationship to vehicle design. This includes the perceptual and cognitive capabilities and limitations of the driver. All types of vehicles (e.g. cars, trucks, trains, aircraft, helicopters, ships, military vehicles) where the task involves monitoring both in-vehicle displays and the surrounding visual environment are included. <br>
Offers of individual papers are invited.  Deadline Friday February 14th.
1997.  Submission by email is preferable, but fax or post is acceptable.
For further information or to be added to the mailing list, please contact:<br>
VIV7, Applied Vision Research Unit, University of Derby<br>             
Tel/Fax: (44)-(0)1332-622287. Email: avru@derby.ac.uk 
Web:  http://www-hcs.derby.ac.uk/avru/viv7

</TD></TR><P>

<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<TD><STRONG>September 22-24, 1997</STRONG>
<BR>Lisbon, Portugal</TD>
<TD><STRONG>TRAFFIC SAFETY ON TWO CONTINENTS</STRONG><br>
 This conference aims to explore emerging research and developments in topics such as incident management, safety audits, use of technologies, data needs, attitudes/values and road safety, traffic engineering, roadway design, high-risk drivers, accident costs and cost/benefit evaluations, traffic laws, traffic control and enforcement techniques. Comparison between Europe and the USA and betwen different parts of Europe will be a special interest. 
A call for Papers has been sent out. Abstracts should be in by January 30.  <br>

The conference is a joint effort of the Swedish Road and Transport Research Institute (VTI), the US Transportation Research Board (TRB), the Forum of European Road Safety Research Institutes (FERSI) and Laboratorio Nacional de Englenharia Civil (LNEC). The conference will include invited formal paper presentations, submitted formal paper presentations and discussion sessions.<br>
<B>Inquiries:</B><br>
<B>US: </B> Dr. Richard Pain, TRB. Tel: + 1 202 334 2960. Fax: + 1 202 334 2003. Telex: 24 86 64 NASW UR<br>
<B>Portugal:</B> Dir. Antonio Macedo or Civ eng Joao Cardoso, LNEC. Tel: +351 1843 2131. Fax: + 351 1840 1580.<br>
<B>Conference secretariat:</B>  Dr. Kenneth Asp, VTI. Tel: + 46 13 20 40 00. Fax: + 46 13 12 61 62. 
</TD></TR><P>




<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<TD><STRONG>August 9-14, 1998</STRONG>
<BR>San Francisco</TD>
<TD><STRONG>THE 24TH INTERNATIONAL CONGRESS OF APPLIED PSYCHOLOGY</STRONG>.
At the 24th International Congress of Applied Psychology, Traffic and Transport will, for the first time, be included as a Division activity. We aim to at least equal the excellent traffic psychology programme of Madrid and 
Kyoto. The call for papers is now out and all members should have received 
this call. If you have not yet received one, please apply to:
icap@apa.org<br>
It is strongly recommended to submit group presentations in the form 
of debate, panels or symposia rather than individual presentations. 
If you are in doubt with regard to submissions, please contact me.<br>
Prof. J.A. Rothengatter
TRC, University of Groningen, NL
E-Mail: J.A.Rothengatter@TRC.RUG.NL

</TD></TR><P>



