<title>BREAKING THE LAW: EDUCATION AND TRAINING FOR YOUNG DRIVER SAFETY</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>BREAKING THE LAW: EDUCATION AND TRAINING FOR YOUNG DRIVER SAFETY</h2>
<p>
<b>Ray Fuller</b>
<p>Irish road safety expert, Dr. Ray Fuller, of Trinity college, Dublin, recently told a
European road safety conference that further training for novice drivers is
essential if their high crash rates are to be reduced. Novice drivers who
have passed their road test are frequently unable to adequately match their
speed to road and traffic conditions, he said.

