<html><head>
<title>BREWERY TEACHES DRIVING SKILLS</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>BREWERY TEACHES DRIVING SKILLS</h2>
<p>
<b></b>
<p> One of the busiest downtown streets in Toronto, Ontario is closed to traffic. Pylons are set up for a driver training program on collision avoidance techniques. The high-profile training effort, presented in conjunction with the city's auto show, was jointly sponsored by a brewery, an auto manufacturer, and a tire company. Both the effectiveness of collision avoidance programs and the wisdom of accepting sponsorship from the alcohol beverage industry are being debated by the driver education community. (Date: 1995; 1,100 words)

