<h2>CANADA'S INSURERS' POSITION ON DRIVER TRAINING</h2>
<p>
<b></b>
<p>In the wake of a new research study called The Role of Driving Experience, the Insurance Bureau of Canada (IBC) has produced some key recommendations on driver testing and training. The study, by the Traffic Injury Research Foundation of Canada, was commissioned by IBC, the major Canadian trade association for property and casualty insurers.(Date: 1995, 950 words)

