<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>DISCOVERY METHOD BOOSTS EGO BUT IT'S NOT GOOD INSTRUCTION</h2>
<p>
<b>Terry Allen, Training Director for Young Drivers of Canada</b>
<p>The "discovery method" of driver training involves taking raw novices and starting them off on a long, straight multi-lane street in moderate to heavy traffic. It has been called the "immersion" approach by its supporters and the "crash and burn" approach by its detractors. (Date: 1995; 700 words)

