<html><head>
<title>DRIVER EDUCATORS SHOULD LOOK TO RESEARCH</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>DRIVER EDUCATORS SHOULD LOOK TO RESEARCH</h2>
<p>
<b></b>
<p>Driving instructors give their students advice about setting their mirrors a certain way, scanning the rearview mirror every five to eight seconds as they drive along, following at a two-second distance, or braking in a certain way. But is that advice based on hard research that links these techniques to increased safety, or is it opinion based on expert drivers' feelings about what makes safer driving?  (Undated, 800 words)

