<html><head>
<title>DRIVER IMPROVEMENT PROGRAMS IN GERMANY</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>DRIVER IMPROVEMENT PROGRAMS IN GERMANY</h2>
<p>
<b></b>
<p>Germany's driver improvement system works. Germany has a system of compulsory medical and psychological examination for drivers who drive while intoxicated and drivers with high demerit points. 
It also has a voluntary educational program which drivers can take to avoid losing their license or to reduce their suspension. 
Every effort has been made to keep the quality of this system high, and some recent studies indicate that these efforts are working. 
This article contains several abstracts of recent studies by German researchers.
