<p>Had it not been for the united efforts of the driving instructors' associations and the many pedagogical, specialist and organizational ideas which they have come up with over the last 40 years, driving instruction in Germany would not have achieved its present high standards. An important role has been played by the ongoing exchange of ideas which has taken place with scientists, politicians and top administrators.

