</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>DRIVING STANDARDS AGENCY CLEARS THE ROAD FOR TEACHERS OF DRIVING THEORY</h2>
<p>
<b></b>
<p>Presently, only Approved Driving Instructors (ADIs) can give professional training to learner drivers in the UK. In July 1996 the UK will conform to European standards with the introduction of a separate theory test. The government anticipates that a broad range of training experts, such as teachers, lecturers and software manufacturers, will wish to develop suitable training courses for learners and have proposed a change in the rules to accommodate this. This article is a summary of the announcement concerning the rule change.
