<html><head>
<title>INSTRUCTIONAL SUPPORT TO DRIVERS</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>INSTRUCTIONAL SUPPORT TO DRIVERS</h2>
<p>
<b>M. J. Kuiken</b>
<p>Given that the traffic environment does not give very good feedback on safety, would driving instructors be able to improve safe performance by providing better feedback about risks? What kind of feedback works best?<BR>
This thesis concludes that instructional support needs to be adapted to the individual driver and that, if it is properly suited to the traffic scenario in question, it can exert a positive influence on driver behavior. <P>
