<html><head>
<title>KAMIKAZES: DRIVERS WITHOUT DRIVER TRAINING</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>KAMIKAZES: DRIVERS WITHOUT DRIVER TRAINING</h2>
<p>
<b>David Thornhill Thompson</b>
<p>In the waning months of the war in the Pacific, the Japanese High Command, lacking long-range bombers, developed a squadron of suicide pilots called kamikazes, or Divine Wind. That was 50 years ago. In 1993, in the U.S., nearly 8,000 young men and women died in machines they didn't know how to "land" either, only this time they were in automobiles, not airplanes. They were taught how to turn the key and turn the wheel but not how to turn an automotive emergency into a safe landing. (Date: 1994; 1,200 words)

