<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>WASHINGTON STATE AT THE LEADING EDGE</h2>
<p>
<b></b>
<p>With a population of about five and a half million and an above-average income level, Washington is a stronghold of high school driver education in the U.S. While many states have lost much, or all, of their funding, Washington has held on (public schools get a subsidy of $137 for every student they graduate), and the state maintains a strong infrastructure of support for its educators. (Date: 1995; 1,200 words)

