<title>IN SEARCH OF SAFER ROADS</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>IN SEARCH OF SAFER ROADS</h2>
<p>
<b></b>
<p>A report just released by the Ontario Ministry of Transportation asks the question "What works and what doesn't work in influencing road user behaviour and improving safety?" The conclusion: "Everything and nothing." The report  reviews models of behaviour change, both in general and those directed specifically to health-related behaviours. "Road user behaviour is so strongly determined that a broad range of influences must be applied to affect lasting change," the report concludes. 
