<html><head>
<title>NEW TO THE ROAD - CONFERENCE PROCEEDINGS</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>NEW TO THE ROAD - CONFERENCE PROCEEDINGS</h2>
<p>
<b></b>
<p><B>New to the Road - Reducing the Risks for Young Motorists</B>
is a 148-page monograph on the proceedings of a conference 
held in June 1995. The conference was organized by the Youth 
Enhancement Service, a part of the Brain Information 
Service of the University of California at Los Angeles and 
the Traffic Injury Research Foundation of Canada under a grant 
provided by the Anheuser-Busch Foundation. This library 
document lists the contents of the monograph and includes 
abstracts of the papers presented. Papers summarize key findings,
review the magnitude of the problem, causes, factors, prevention 
programs and policies, training and licensing options.
