<html><head>
<title>SOUTH AFRICA TAKES STEPS TO COMBAT FATALITIES</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>SOUTH AFRICA TAKES STEPS TO COMBAT FATALITIES</h2>
<p>
<b>Driver/Education, 1993</b>
<p>Comparing traffic crash statistics between one country and another is a tricky business. A lot depends on how crashes and fatality rates are defined, on driving conditions, and on whether the comparison is based on miles driven, population, or number of cars. No matter how the comparison is set up, the Republic of South Africa comes out at  or near the top of the list. Its fatality rate of 11.4 per 100 million km driven compares with 1.45 for the USA and 1.8 for Japan.

<p><img align="middle" src="/icons/view-full.gif">
<a href="/pde/ARTICLES/free/safric-952245560.html"> VIEW FULL TEXT</a><p>
