<html><head>
<title>THE ENVIRONMENT AND THE DRIVING INSTRUCTOR</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>THE ENVIRONMENT AND THE DRIVING INSTRUCTOR</h2>
<p>
<b>PROFESSOR ADOLPH-EUGEN BONGARD</b>
<p>Traffic safety educators have, up to now, been almost exclusively concerned with the safety problems caused by automobiles. But perhaps we should widen the view and see the larger picture of the dangers for all of us that result merely from the fact that millions of automobiles are driven on our earth, and that more and more automobiles are being driven daily by more and more people (Date: 1993, 1,900 words)

