<title>TOWARDS A SOCIOLOGY OF TRAFFIC</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>TOWARDS A SOCIOLOGY OF TRAFFIC</h2>
<p>
<b>By J. Peter Rothe</b>
<p>If we assume that motoring is a social activity and that streets are social arenas, then we must acknowledge the social conditions that impact driving. That is not to say we dismiss valuable learning produced by psychologists, epidemiologists, legal experts, and driving professionals. <p
