<html><head>
<title>TRAFFIC VIOLATOR SCHOOL RESEARCH REPORT</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<h2>TRAFFIC VIOLATOR SCHOOL RESEARCH REPORT</h2>
<p>
<b>By Michael Finigan, Ph.D., April, 1995</b>
<p>This study was commissioned by the Santa Clara County, California Municipal Court and was designed to examine two issues. The first is the curriculum effect - the effectiveness of the NTSI curriculum (Levels I and II) in reducing subsequent recidivism, particularly accidents, for its participants when compared to a no-treatment control group. The second is the program effect - the effectiveness of the NTSI program in reducing subsequent accidents for its participants compared to drivers who are eligible to attend the program but who chose not to take the TVS dismissal route and to pay the fine for the violation instead.<p
<p><img align="middle" src="/icons/view-full.gif">
<a href="/pde/ARTICLES/restricted/violator-952255968.html"> VIEW FULL TEXT</a><p>
