<head><title>New Driver Car Control Clinic</title></head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" text="000044" link="0000ff" vlink="660099">
<center>
<IMG SRC="ccl3.gif" ALT="The New Driver Car Control Clinic"><P></center>
<H3><A NAME="improve">Why The New Driver</A> Car Control Clinic Will Improve <BR>Your New Driver's Chances of Avoiding Those Early Accidents</H3>
<table>
<tr><td><UL><LI>Driving is a psychomotor skill, just like baseball or playing the piano. In an emergency all the body's reactions are governed by the subconscious mind, not the conscious mind. Therefore, just like an athlete or musician, the subconscious must be pre-programmed through practice exercises.</ul></td>
<TD><IMG SRC="cccars2.GIF" alt="New Driver Car Control Clinic vehicles"></TD></TR>
<TR><TD colspan=2>
<ul>
<LI>
<STRONG>The New Driver Car Control Clinic</STRONG> presents 10 exercises, fully diagrammed and illustrated in the Workbook and Video that, when practiced, give the New Driver's subconscious the proper information to react appropriately in an emergency.</UL></TD>
<tr valign=top><TD colspan=2>
<ul><LI>
The exercises contained in <STRONG>The New Driver Car Control Clinic</STRONG> are meant to be practiced in a parking lot at 20 mph or less. Detailed instructions and step-by-step directions are contained in the Workbook and Video.</UL></td></tr>

</tr></table> <P>

<table><tr><td><IMG SRC="dave2.gif" alt="Dave Thompson"></td>
<td>
Founder and author <STRONG>David Thompson</STRONG> is an automotive journalist and championship-winning racing driver who developed <STRONG>The New Driver Car Control Clinic</STRONG> using many of the car control techniques employed by professional drivers.</td></tr></table><P>
<P><IMG SRC="redbar2.GIF" ALT="----------------------"><P>

