<H3>(V&Auml;GVERKET)</H3>

<IMG SRC="sweden.GIF" ALT="Swedish National Road Administration">

<H3>Licensing, Testing, and Development Division<br>
of the Drivers License Department</h3>
<P>
<IMG SRC="marbthin.gif" ALT="------------------------">
<P>
<blockquote>
The Swedish National Road Administration is responsible for all matters in connection with road traffic, including safety, licensing, and record keeping for all license holders in Sweden.<P>

The Drivers License Department is nationally responsible for the licensing of drivers. This includes training curriculum, examinations, and supervision of traffic schools.<P>

<H3>Address:</H3>
Swedish National Road Administration<BR>
S-781 87<BR>
Sweden<br>

Tel.: +46 243 75 000<BR>
Fax: +46 243 75 193<P>

<H3>Staff</H3>
<B>Christer Drangel</B> (Department Head)<BR>
Responsibilities include: overall responsibility for the 29 local
Driving License offices in Sweden, the national register for license holders, and the head office.<BR>
Tel: +46 243 75 319<BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:christer.drangel@vv.se">christer.drangel@vv.se</A><P>
<STRONG>Hans Mattsson</STRONG><BR>
Responsibilities include: development and evaluation of the examination procedures and construction of the theory tests. <BR>
Tel: +46 243 75 249  <BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:hans.mattsson@vv.se">hans.mattsson@vv.se</A><P>

<STRONG>Per-Olov Grummas Granstr&ouml;m</STRONG><BR>
Responsibilities include: development and evaluation concerning<BR>
curriculum, organization and quality of education, teacher education.  <BR>
Tel: +46 243 75 224 <BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:per-olov.grummas@vv.se">per-olov.grummas@vv.se</A><P>
</blockquote>
