<h3><A NAME="drive">Drive Michigan safely</A></h3><P>
A two-year safe driving campaign in Michigan state is putting primary emphasis on driver courtesy. &quot;Drivers must have the skills and knowledge they need to be good drivers and that is why the State Safety Commission is encouraging motorists to give more thought to the driving experience and to exercising courtesy,&quot; said Secretary of State Richard H. Austin. <P>
There has been increasing public concern in Michigan about discourteous drivers. The Transportation Association of Michigan (TSAM) is exploring the possibility of establishing &quot;courtesy clubs&quot; to encourage drivers to clean up their act. &quot;Any comments and suggestions for the campaign are welcome,&quot; says TSAM President Thomas Reel. <P>
