<h2>COMING EVENTS</h2><HR><p>

<H3>TEXAS</H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
The Texas Driver &#38; Traffic Safety Education Association (TDTSEA) will 
hold its annual conference on April 12th and 13th, 1996, at the Clarion 
Hotel in Richardson, Texas.  Driver Education instructors and others 
with interests in traffic safety are invited to attend.<P>

The Clarion is a nice conference hotel (1-800-CLARION for reservations) 
and is located a few miles north of Interstate Loop 635, around Dallas.<P>

On-site registration is welcomed.  However, there will be a small, 
additional charge for late registration.   For more information or a 
TDTSEA membership application, write to:<P>
Benney B. Raley, Executive Secretary<BR>
TDTSEA<BR>
P. O. Box 1350<BR>
Huntsville, TX  77342-1350<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>CALIFORNIA</H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
The California Association for Safety Education will hold its annual 
conference in Friday and Saturday May 3rd and 4th, 1996, at the Holiday 
Inn, Capitol Plaza, Sacramento, California.<P>

The conference is planning sessions of particular interest to traffic 
safety and driver education teachers, as well as supervisors and 
administrators.<P>

For information, contact Jim Lewis, President, at Fax (805) 520-6633.<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>MONTANA</H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
The Montana Traffic Education Association will be hosting its annual spring 
conference&#47;workshop for Traffic Safety Education Teachers  and related 
personnel at the Heritage Inn, 1700 Fox Farm Rd, Great Falls, Montana, on 
May 5th, 6th and 7th, 1996. The conference theme is &quot;Preparing for 
Tomorrow&quot;. For information, contact Terry Grant, President, at Tel: (406) 395-4031.


</BLOCKQUOTE>
