<h2>Welcome to the Hamilton-Niagara<BR>Regional Chapter<BR>of the Council of Driver Trainers</h2><P>



<BLOCKQUOTE>The Council of Driver Trainers and Safety Professionals is an association

of Driver Trainers working in co-operation with the Transportation Safety

Association of Ontario to promote safety within the transportation and

transport industry.<P>



The Council encourages the improvement of driver behavior through increased

awareness and training. Working with goverment agencies, provincial police

departments, and private organizations, the council strives for a uniform

system of safety requirements for all commercial drivers in Ontario.<P>



The Council of Driver Trainers is open to all individuals concerned with

promoting safety within the transportation industry.<P>



Current members include:<p>


<UL>
<b>Driver Trainers<br>

Directors of Safety<br>

Risk Managers<br>

Labour Safety Personnel<br>

Individuals concerned with Occupational Health &#38; Safety</b></UL><p>





<b>JOIN YOUR PEERS ...</b><P>



Members must be employed in the motor vehicle transportation industry as a

safety supervisor, driver trainer, driver supervisor or associated with any

goverment sponsored agency, police department, municipality, or insurance

company.<P>



Chapters have representation from local, regional, and O.P.P. police forces

as well as from the Ministry of Transportation.<P>



<b>SHARE IDEAS ...</b><p>



Chapter meetings are held monthly. Members have the opportunity to learn

more about safety within the industry by sharing ideas and information with

other companies and individuals.<P>

If YOU want more input into the way safety is handled within the

transportation industry, join us on the Council of Driver Trainers.<P>

There are several chapters of the Council of Driver Trainers.<P>



