<html>
<head>
<META name="description" content="Red River Water Management Consortium - a group of Business, Environmental, Civic and Educational Leaders">
<META name="keywords" content="Water, Resources, North Dakota, Minnesota, Technology, Agriculture, Hydrogeology">
<META name="author" content="Roy Beard">
<title>Water Management</title>
</head>
<BODY Bgcolor=ffffff Background="/gif/backgrnd.gif">
<center>
<Table Width=600 CellPadding=0>
<TR>
<TD Valign=Top>


<Table Width=200>
<TR><TD><a href="../index.html"><img src ="../gif/logo_1.gif" align="center" border=0 ALT="EERC Logo"></a><p></TD></TR>
<TR><TD><a href=<a href="http://www.rrtrade.org/agvise/index.htm"><img src ="../gif/agvis2.gif" align="center" border=0 ALT="Agvise Logo"></a></TD></TR>
</center>
</Table>
</TD>

<TD>
<Table Width=400>
<TR><TD>
<img src="../gif/rrlogo1.gif"><br>

</Table>
</TD>
</TR>
</Table><hr>
<img src="../gif/rbas2.gif"></center>
<hr size =4>
<Font Size=+2><b>I</b></font>ntelligent use and management of water resources are required to ensure 
sufficient, quality water for public use and future development of industry 
and agriculture in the Basin of the Red River of the North.  Available water 
is limited in the Red River Basin.  There is a great need to care for the 
supplies available and identify the various management options available.  
Water quality is as important as quantity.  The quality of water resources 
in the Basin must be determined with respect to potential contaminants, thus 
establishing a baseline for future use.  Once a baseline is established, 
changes in water quality can be monitored, and solutions to problems encountered 
can be determined.  This program was developed to establish a consortium of 
industries, municipalities, and other regional entities in partnership with 
state and federal governments to address important issues that may impact 
the areas water resources.  A watershed management program such as this 
can be used to respond to environmental and water quantity concerns with 
technical solutions while allowing for community and economic development.
<p>
<hr size=4>
