<HEAD>
<TITLE>Partners</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body><BODY Bgcolor=ffffff Background="/gif/bkgrnd.jpg">
<Img Src="/gif/eerc_hd.gif">

<Table Width=600 CellPadding=0>
<TR>
<TD Valign=Top>
<Table Width=240>
<TR><TD><Img Src="/gif/oleary2.gif" Border=0></A></TD></TR>
<TR><TD><a href="../index.html"><img src="../gif/home.gif" border=0></a><a href="partop.htm"><img src="../gif/next.gif" border=0></a>
</TD></TR>
</Table>
</TD>

<TD>
<Table Width=375>
<TR><TD><Font Size=-1><h1>Developing Partnerships</h1>
<hr>
</center>
Partnerships are key to solving complex energy and environmental problems and developing innovative energy and environmental technologies.  To bring an idea through the rigorous stages of research, development, demonstration, and commercialization, a cohesive team of people possessing distinctive skills and disciplines is needed.
<p>
The EERC is committed to a philosophy of RDD&C. In partnership with private industry, government agencies, research organizations, and academic institutions, the EERC conducts research and development of practical, problem-solving technologies and processes--RD.  It demonstrates those technologies and processes in the field--the second D.  Finally, working with its industrial partners, it seeks to commercialize successful technologies and processes--C.
<p>
Developing energy and environmental technologies is neither quick nor inexpensive.  It can take several years to develop and then successfully demonstrate a technology.  The cost can reach well into the millions of dollars.  By the time an idea is commercialized, a project team often includes government and private research organizations, scientists, research managers, laboratory technicians, engineers, engineering technicians, venture capitalists, investors, market analysts, entrepreneurs, marketers, business managers, accountants, patent and copyright counsel, legal counsel, elected officials, and regulatory agencies.
<p>
Commercializing energy and environmental technologies holds the potential for significant returns, however.  The EERC is willing to make the long-term investment and take the risks to seize these opportunities.

The EERC extends an invitation for partnership ventures to anyone seeking research, development, demonstration, and commercialization opportunities focused on energy and environmental technologies.
<p>
<hr>


</Table>
</TD>
</TR>
</Table>







