<TR><TD><Font Size=-1>
<h1>Coal</h1><hr></center>

Coal will continue to play a major role in meeting world energy demands well into the 21st century. The EERC has more than four decades of basic and applied coal research, with particular emphasis on low-rank coals.   Today, the EERC is the world's leading low-rank coal research center.   EERC coal research pursues a scientific understanding of the physical, chemical, and mineralogical nature of coal as the foundation for predictively engineering coal conversion technologies and power systems.   From fundamental resource characterization to waste utilization or disposal, EERC coal research allows coal to be used more cleanly and efficiently in existing facilities as well as in emerging technologies.  
<p>
<h2>Key Coal Activities</h2>
<ul plain>
<li>Evaluation and Characterization
<li>Fuel Upgrading
<li>Direct and Indirect Coal Liquefaction
<li>Conventional Gasification
<li>Underground Coal Gasification
<li>Advanced Gasification
<li>Repowering
<li>Fuel Quality Impacts on Power System Performance
<li>Advanced Power Systems
<li>Atmospheric Emission Control
<li>Waste Utilization and Disposal
<li>Reclamation of Disturbed Lands
<li>Analytical Methods Development
<li>Groundwater
<li>Contaminant Cleanup and Site Remediation
</ul>
<p><hr>
