<Table Width=370>
<TR><TD><Font Size=-1>
<h2>Oil</h2><hr></center>

The EERC provides the oil industry with a variety of services and technologies.  These include the cleanup of water produced during drilling operations, petroleum desulfurization using bioremediation, site characterization, waste utilization expertise, and contaminant characterization, transport, and fate assessment. The EERC has more than three decades of practical field and laboratory experience in environmental issues currently facing the oil industry.  It also has several decades of experience with organic liquids and alternative oils such as methyl ester diesel fuel.   
<p>
<h2>Key Oil Activities</h2>
<ul plain>
<li><a href="../nafl/nafl.htm">National Alternative Fuels Laboratory</a>
<li>Vegetable Oil Diesel Fuel
<li>Produced-Water Management
<li>Naturally Occurring Radioactive Material
<li>Mercury in Groundwater and Atmospheric Emissions
<li>Direct Coal Liquefaction
<li>Indirect Coal Liquefaction
<li>Plastics Recycling and Depolymerization
<li>Combustion Testing
<li>Atmospheric Emission Control 
<li>Waste Utilization and Disposal
<li>Petroleum Coke Testing
<li>Contaminant Cleanup and Site Remediation
<li>Groundwater Research for the North American Gas and Oil Industry
<li>Applied Geology
</ul>
