<head>
<title>Nonfuel Carbon Products</title>

</head>
<body><BODY Bgcolor=ffffff Background="/gif/bkgrnd.jpg">
<Img Src="/gif/eerc_hd.gif">

<Table Width=600 CellPadding=0>
<TR>
<TD Valign=Top>
<Table Width=220>
<TR><TD><Img Src="/gif/lab.gif" Border=0></A></TD></TR>
<TR><TD><a href="ren.htm"><img src="../gif/back.gif" border=0></a><a href="aps.htm"><img src="../gif/next.gif" border=0></a><a href="../index.html"><img src="../gif/home.gif" border=0></a>
</TD></TR>
</Table>
</TD>

<TD>
<Table Width=400
>
<TR><TD><Font Size=-1>
<h2>Nonfuel Carbon Products</h2>
<hr></center>
Carbon compounds are useful in many products. Carbon fiber, for instance, is used in structural components of automobiles and aircraft.   Nonfuel products from coal and other sources will play an increasingly greater role in our economy.   By understanding the fundamental nature of carbon compounds, EERC nonfuel carbon product research is seeking to take advantage of the chemical treasure trove inherent in coal and other sources. 
<p>
<h2>Key Nonfuel Carbon Products Activities</h2>
<ul plain>
<li>Production of Form Coke and Activated Carbon Sorbents 
<li>Pyrolysis
<li>Liquefaction of Carbon Compounds
<li>Waste Utilization and Disposal
<li>Chemicals from Coal and Other Carbon Compounds
</ul><p>
<hr>
