<head>
<title>Advanced Power Systems</title>

</head>
<body><BODY Bgcolor=ffffff Background="/gif/bkgrnd.jpg">
<Img Src="/gif/eerc_hd.gif">

<Table Width=600 CellPadding=0>
<TR>
<TD Valign=Top>
<Table Width=200>
<TR><TD><Img Src="/gif/repair_m.gif" Border=0></A></TD></TR>
<TR><TD><a href="nonc.htm"><img src="../gif/back.gif" Border=0></a><a href="ams.htm"><img src="../gif/next.gif" Border=0></a><a href="../index.html"><img src="../gif/home.gif" Border=0></a>
</TD></TR>
</Table>
</TD>

<TD>
<Table Width=410
>
<TR><TD><Font Size=-1>
<h2>Advanced Power Systems</h2><hr></center>

Advanced power systems are providing clean, efficient energy from coal and other sources.  Advanced power systems research at the EERC embraces a wide spectrum of energy conversion and use technologies.   Thousands of existing energy systems in coming years will require retrofitting and upgrading to extend their useful lives. In addition, more efficient and environmentally compatible energy technologies are being introduced.   From retrofitting current facilities to developing advanced power systems for coal and non-carbon-based energy, the EERC is committed to discovering ways to produce the most power and the least waste.  

<h2>Key Advanced Power Systems Activities</h2>
<ul plain>
<li>Fuel Utilization
<li>Pressurized Combustion
<li>Hot-Gas Cleaning
<li>Advanced Gasification
<li>Particulate Control
<li>Waste Utilization and Disposal
<li>Fluidized-Bed Technologies
<li>Waste Conversion
<li>Waste to Energy
<li>Plastics Recycling
</ul><p>
<h3>Contact People</h3>

