<Table Width=380>
<TR><TD><Font Size=-1>
<h2>Research Facilities and Equipment</h2><hr></center>

To conduct meaningful and productive research, it is necessary to provide dedicated scientists and engineers with state-of-the-art research tools.   The EERC strives to provide the best possible combination of equipment, laboratory space, talent, and leadership. With the completion of a $7.6 million expansion in 1994, EERC laboratory, technology demonstration, and office space increased to 169,000 square feet dedicated to energy and environmental research, development, demonstration, and commercialization. The EERC maintains a wide range of laboratories and equipment for solid, liquid, and gaseous characterization of the physical, chemical, mineralogical, biological, hydrological, and geological properties of natural and synthetic materials and processes.  These highly sophisticated and diverse tools can be used in a variety of research programs.  This provides for effective utilization of instrumentation and facilities and fosters a cross-fertilization of ideas and solutions for analogous situations between research programs.
<p>
<h2>Laboratories</h2>
<ul plain>
<li>Applied Chemistry and Analytical Research
<li>Applied Geology 
<li>Coal Analysis 
<li>Coal By-Products Utilization 
<li>Coal Sciences
<li>Environmental Microbiology
<li>Fuels Analysis 
<li>Fuels Research 
<li>Gas Chromatography/Mass Spectrometry 
<li>Groundwater Research 
<li>High-Temperature Research
<li>Materials Properties Research 
<li>National Alternative Fuels
<li>Natural Materials Analytical Research 
<li>Nuclear Magnetic Resonance 
<li>Particulate Research
<li>Reclamation Research
<li>Remediation Research 
<li>Solids, Liquids, and Gas Analysis 
<li>Thermal Analysis 
<li>Turbine Simulation
</ul>	 
<h2>Technology Demonstration Capabilities</h2>
<ul plain>	
<li>High-Temperature/Pressure Reactor Systems
<li>Pulverized Fuel Combustors
Atmospheric Fluidized-Bed Combustors
Pressurized Fluidized-Bed Reactors
<li>Pressurized Pneumatic Transport Reactors
<li>Wet Carbonization Reactor System
<li>Laminar Flow Combustion System
<li>Fabric Filters
<li>Electrostatic Precipitators
<li>Pressure Design Engineering and Equipment Fabrication
</ul>

<p>
