<html>
<head>
<META name="description" content="Red River Water Management Consortium - a group of Business, Environmental, Civic and Educational Leaders">
<META name="keywords" content="Water, Resources, North Dakota, Minnesota, Technology, Agriculture, Hydrogeology">
<META name="author" content="Roy Beard">
<title>Water Management</title>
</head>
<body background="../gif/backgrnd.gif">
<Img Src="/gif/banner2.gif">
<hr>
<H2>Approach</H2>
<hr>
<img src="../gif/water10.GIF"><br>
<font size=+2><b>T</b></font>he Energy & Environmental Research Center (EERC) and AGVISE Laboratories, Inc., have 
teamed to develop a water management program for the Red River of the North Basin.  A 
consortium of vested stockholders has been formed to assist in the development of the 
program, define current critical issues, and provide direction for the annual work plan.  
Fees obtained from consortium members will be used to perform work on issues pertaining 
to the development of a long-term watershed management strategy, to solve water-related 
problems that exist in the basin, and to obtain federal and state funds where a match is 
required.  Issues identified for the region will be addressed to find economical, 
practical, and timely solutions.  These solutions will be accomplished through optimizing 
and improving processes and practices currently being used, evaluating technology options, 
and identifying new or novel technologies to solve problems.  The overall goal of the 
program is to develop a long-term watershed management strategy focusing on water 
quality and quantity.
<p>
<hr>
        |<a href="index.html">Home Page</a> | <a href="workp.html">Next Section</a>|

