<head>
<title>Hot-Water Extraction of Nonpolar
Organic Pollutants from Soils</title>
</head>
<body>
<body background = "../gif/drops1.jpg">
<center><center><img src="gifs/eerc_hd.gif"></center>
<h1>Hot-Water Extraction of Nonpolar Organic Pollutants from Soils </h1>
</center>
<hr>
<h2>Background</h2>
<p>
     Supercritical water is an effective extraction fluid for polar and nonpolar organic pollutants, but is
corrosive and requires pressures (&gt;221 bar) and temperatures (&gt;374&#176;C) that make its use
prohibitive.  However, the attractive solvent characteristics for organic pollutants in water can be achieved at
much lower pressures (a few bars) and temperatures (e.g., &lt;250&#176;C).  Preliminary experiments have
demonstrated that many polar and nonpolar organic pollutants can be solvated in water under these
relatively mild conditions.<p> 

<h2>Objectives</h2>
<p>
     The temperature and pressure ranges that can effectively use  water to extract organic pollutants
such as polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (PAHs) and polychorinated biphenyls (PCBs) were determined.<p>
<p>
<h2>Results</h2>
<p>
     Results demonstrated that PAHs and PCBs can be efficiently extracted from soil using pressures aslow as
50 bar and temperatures as low as 250&#176;C.  More polar pollutants can be extracted at even lower
temperatures.  When water is pressurized to the liquid state at 250&#176;C, the extraction is very selective for
PAHs, and alkanes of similar vapor pressures are not extracted.  However, when the pressure is dropped so
that the water is steam, both PAHs and alkanes are extracted.  PCBs can be extracted in as little as 5 minutes
from soil using only hot water as the extraction fluid.  This preliminary work demonstrated that hot water has
great potential for both analytical- and remediation-scale extractions of organic pollutants from soil. 
Peer-reviewed publications describing the results of this investigation are available upon request. <p>
<br><br>
<hr>
<b>Project Manager:</b> Steven B. Hawthorne/<a href=mailto:shawthorne@eerc.und.nodak.edu>shawthorne@eerc.und.nodak.edu </a> <br>
<b>Phone:</b> (701) 777-5256 <br>
<b>Informacion en espa&#241;ol:</b> Lucia Romuld/<a href=mailto:lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu>lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu</a><br>
<b>Phone:</b> 1-701-777-5223<br>
<b>Sponsor:</b>
<li> U.S. Department of Energy Morgantown Energy Technology
Center <br>
<b>Duration of Project:</b>
<li> March 1994 to March 1995 
