<head>
<title>Evaluation of a Bituminous Coal-Water
Fuel</title>
</head>
<body><center><img src="gifs/eerc_hd.gif"></center><center>
<h2>Evaluation of a Bituminous Coal-Water Fuel </h2>
</center>
<hr>

<h3>Background</h3>

     Coal fines produced during normal operation of a bituminous coal-washing facility are discarded
at considerable cost.  Recovery of these coal fines as a coal-water fuel to provide supplemental
heat to steam generators and utility boilers appears to be the most cost-effective approach.  The
current emphasis is to recover washing fines and blend them with the washery product to prepare
a stable coal-water fuel.<p>
<h3>Objectives</h3>
     Project objectives include the following:<p>
<ul plain>
<IMG SRC="GIFS/bl_dot.gif">Prepare a stable bituminous coal-water fuel and evaluate its rheological
properties</br>
<p>
<IMG SRC="GIFS/bl_dot.gif"> Determine flame stability properties of the fuel as a function of residence time
and firing rate<br>
<p>
<IMG SRC="GIFS/bl_dot.gif"> Determine combustion efficiency as a function of residence time and firing
rate<br>
<p>
<IMG SRC="GIFS/bl_dot.gif"> Perform limited evaluation of the fuel's fouling potential<br>
<p>
<IMG SRC="GIFS/bl_dot.gif"> Characterize emissions of CO, CO<sub>2</sub>, O<sub>2</sub>,
SO<sub>2</sub>, and NO<sub>x</sub><br>
</ul>
<p>
 <h3>Results</h3> 
     At the time of this printing, the tests had not yet been completed.  Testing is expected to be
completed by the end of August 1995.
<hr>
<b>Project Manager:</b> Jay R. Gunderson/<a href=mailto:jgunderson@eerc.und.nodak.edu>jgunderson@eerc.und.nodak.edu </a> <br>
<b>Phone:</b> (701) 777-5258 <br>
<b>Sponsor:</b>Prairie View A&amp;M University <br>
<b>Duration of Project:</b>May 1995 to September 1995 <br>
