<html>
<head>
<title>Effect of Ethanol Denaturant on Gasoline
RVP</title>
</head>
<body>
<body background = "../gif/drops1.jpg">
<center><center><img src="gifs/eerc_hd.gif"></center>
<h1>Effect of Ethanol Denaturant on Gasoline RVP</h1></center>
<hr>
<p>
<h2>Background </h2>
     Preparation of a mixture of 10% ethanol in gasoline (E10) results in a vapor pressure (VP) that
is higher than either the ethanol or the gasoline individually.  As a result of the increased
vapor pressure, increased levels of volatile organic compounds (VOC) are released to the
atmosphere causing a reduction in air quality.  However, the hydrophilic nature of ethanol and
the choice of the denaturant added to the ethanol to make it unfit for human consumption may
be at least partially responsible for the increased VP.  Denaturants legal for use in gasoline are
light hydrocarbons, which themselves have high Reid vapor pressure (RVP) relative to
gasoline.  Actual denaturants used in denaturing commercial fuel ethanol are liquified natural
gas and regular unleaded gasoline.<p>
<p>
<h2>Objective</h2>
<p>
     The objective of this project was to determine the role of water and ethanol denaturant in
increasing the RVP of a gasoline-ethanol blend.<p>
<p>
<h2>Results</h2>
<p>
     Both water and some of the legal denaturants were shown to cause an increase in the vapor
pressure of both gasoline and gasoline-ethanol blends.  The addition of absolute (undenatured)
ethanol to gasoline resulted in a 0.8- to 1.0-psig increase in RVP.  Addition of denatured ethanol
tended to increase the RVP 0.1 to 0.3 psig above the initial 0.8 to 1.0 psig.  The additional
increase in RVP was attributed to the presence of denaturants in the alcohol.  Addition of water
to E10 blends resulted in a 0.1- to 0.4 psig increase in RVP.<p>
<p>
     The protocol followed and the results of this work were summarized in an article entitled "Vapor
Pressure Response to Denaturant and Water in E10 Blends," in the January 1995 edition of the
<i>Journal of the Air and Waste Management Association</i>.<p>
<hr>
<b>Project Manager:</b> Curtis L. Knudson/<a href=mailto:cknudson@eerc.und.nodak.edu>cknudson@eerc.und.nodak.edu </a> <br>
<b>Phone:</b> (701) 777-5185<br>
<b>Informacion en espa&#241;ol:</b> Lucia Romuld/<a href=mailto:lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu>lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu</a><br>
<b>Phone:</b> 1-701-777-5223<br>
<b>Sponsors:</b>
<li>National Corn Growers Association
<li>U.S. Department of Energy Morgantown Energy Technology Center<br>
<b>Duration of Project:</b>
<li>July 1993 to December 1993<br>
