<head>
<title>Wastepaper Pellets as a Source of Fuel
for Auxiliary Home Heating</title>
</head>
<body><center><img src="gifs/eerc_hd.gif"></center>
<center>
<h1>Wastepaper Pellets as a Source of Fuel for Auxiliary Home Heating</h1></center>
<hr>
<h2>Background</h2>
<p>
     Paper and paper products make up the largest part of the municipal solid waste stream.  Solid
waste diversion through recycling is effective at reducing the quantity of material which requires
ultimate disposal.  However, supply and demand dictates the total quantity of material which can
be economically recycled. Currently only certain types of paper products are acceptable for
recycling, and the markets for many of these are depressed because of oversupply.  An
opportunity exists to reduce the volume of paper entering the waste stream and to produce a
salable product.  The technology exists to produce densified refuse-derived fuel pellets from
various grades of paper and paper products for use in pellet stoves for auxiliary home heating. 
However, because of a limited amount of available data, various parameters such as ash, sulfur,
chloride, and heavy metals contents must be quantified and actual combustion data must be
generated so that the combustion performance of wastepaper pellets can be compared to that of
existing, commercially available wood pellet fuels.<p>
<h2>Objectives</h2>
     The objectives of this project are to determine the types of waste paper that would make the best
pellets from a combustion standpoint and to define the combustion characteristics of one or two
types of wastepaper pellet fuels in a representative combustion system.<p>
<h2>Results</h2>

     A representative wood pellet stove has been obtained and instrumented for the proposed work. 
Three types of wood pellet fuels have been procured and used for shakedown testing of the stove. 
Laboratory and combustion testing of the wastepaper pellet fuels will be completed as soon as
they can be produced and delivered.
<p><br>
<hr>
<B>Project Manager:</B> Thomas A. Moe/<a href=mailto:tmoe@eerc.und.nodak.edu>tmoe@eerc.und.nodak.edu </a> <br>
<B>Phone:</b> (701) 777-5231<br>
<b>Informacion en espa&#241;ol:</b> Lucia Romuld/<a href=mailto:lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu>lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu</a><br>
<b>Phone:</b> 1-701-777-5223<br>
<b>Sponsors:</b>
<li>U.S. Department of Energy<br>
<li>Western Regional Biomass Energy Program of the Western Area Power Administration<br>
<b>Duration of Project:</b>
<li>March 1994 to June 1995<p>
<center><img src="gifs/eerc_hd.gif"></center>
