<head>
<title>Geotechnical and Geochemical 
Characterization of Advanced Coal
Process Wastes</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><img src="gifs/eerc_hd.gif"><br>
<h2>Geotechnical and Geochemical Characterization of Advanced Coal Process Wastes </h2>
</center> 
<hr>


<font color="#990066"><h3> <b>Background</b> </h3></font> <p>

<p>

     Effective management of wastes from advanced coal utilization processes requires a detailed
understanding of the physical properties of the waste streams.  This project was undertaken to
develop chemical and mineralogical property data for a variety of advanced process wastes and
to evaluate the suitability of different management practices for the wastes.  These materials
were collected by the U.S. Department of Energy (DOE) over a period of several years and
originate from a variety of projects.  This effort completed the characterization database for
these materials.<p>

<p>

<font color="#990066"><h3> <b>Objective</b> </h3></font> <p>

<p>

     The objective of this project was to characterize the disposal-related properties of a wide range
of different waste materials produced from advanced coal utilization processes.<p>

<p>

<font color="#990066"><h3> <b>Results</b> </h3></font> <p>

<p>

     Eight solid wastes collected from various facilities employing advanced coal combustion and
coal conversion technologies were characterized for this work.  The characterization protocol
used for each waste included an extensive set of waste management-related physical properties,
bulk chemical analyses, and mineral analyses.  The characterizations of the eight advanced
process wastes were completed, and the results are summarized in a technical report.  The
most significant disposal-related property exhibited by many of the advanced process wastes
was the self-heating behavior when they were conditioned with water.  Work on the first eight
advanced process wastes was completed in 1993.<p>
<hr>
<b>Project Manager:</b>  Charles J. Moretti/<a href=mailto:cmoretti@eerc.und.nodak.edu>cmoretti@eerc.und.nodak.edu </a> <br>
<b>Phone:</b>  (701) 777-5150<br>
<b>Sponsor:</b>  Universal Fuel Development  Associates
<br> (under contract to
U.S.  Department of Energy Morgantown  Energy Technology
Center )<br>
<b>Duration of Project:</b>  September 1989 to October
1993</b><p>

