<head>
<title>Centrifugal Membrane Filtration</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><img src="gifs/eerc_hd.gif"><br>
<h1>Centrifugal Membrane Filtration</h1> </center>
<hr>
<h2>Background</h2>
<p>
     The EERC will team with SpinTek Systems,  LP, a small business and owner of a novel
centrifugal membrane filtration technology, to establish the applicability of the technology to
U.S. Department of Energy (DOE) site remediation and the commercial viability of the
technology for liquid mixed-waste-stream remediation.  The technology is a uniquely
configured process that utilizes ultrafiltration and microporous membranes at pressures of up
to 100 psig in combination with centrifugal force to remove suspended and dissolved solids to
as low as 200 molecular weight.<p>
<p>
<h2>Objective</h2>
<p>
     The overall project consists of several integrated research phases related to the applicability,
continued development, demonstration, and commercialization of the SpinTek centrifugal
membrane filtration process.  Specific objectives of Phase I research activities include 1) a
problem and opportunity assessment to identify applicable waste streams associated with DOE
sites, 2) the development of detailed process data that will provide information with regard to
the application of the technology at DOE sites, 3) testing and evaluation of a laboratory
centrifugal membrane filtration unit using surrogate waste streams under a variety of operating
conditions, and 4) the development of process data that will allow optimization of the
technology for appropriate DOE waste streams.<p>

<p><h2>Results</h2>

     The project is scheduled to begin in the near future.
<p>
<hr>
<b>Project Manager:</b>Daniel J. Stepan/<a href=mailto:dstepan@eerc.und.nodak.edu>dstepan@eerc.und.nodak.edu </a> <br>
<b>Phone:</b> (701) 777-5247<br>
<b>Informacion en espa&#241ol:</b> Lucia Romuld/<a href=mailto:lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu>lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu</a><br>
<b>Phone:</b> 1-701-777-5223<br>
<b>Sponsor:</b>
<li>U.S. Department of Energy Morgantown Energy Technology  Center<br>
<b>Duration of Project:</b>
<li> June 1995 to September 1996 
