<head>
<title>Solventless Extraction of Organic Pollutants from Water with Solid-Phase 
Microextraction</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><img src="gifs/eerc_hd.gif"><br>
<h1>Solventless Extraction of Organic Pollutants from Water with Solid-Phase Microextraction
</h1></center>
<hr>
<h2>Background</h2>
<p>
     The analysis of organic pollutants in water currently requires extraction with large volumes of
halogenated solvents.  Solid-phase microextraction (SPME) can allow direct extraction of the
pollutants into a solid phase, with no need for liquid solvents.  The analytes are then
determined by conventional gas chromatography or spectroscopic techniques.<p>
<p>
<h2>Objective</h2>
<p>
     The theoretical basis and practical applications of SPME with gas chromatographic analysis
are being developed.  In addition, a new approach using direct spectroscopic determination of
organic pollutants absorbed from water samples is being investigated.<p>
<p>
<h2>Results</h2>
<p>
     SPME with gas chromatography has been demonstrated to give better detection limits for
polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (PAHs) and related pollutants than conventional techniques,
while requiring no organic solvent and much less time.  Detection limits for PAHs in water
range from &lt;1 ppb for low-molecular-weight aromatics (e.g.,naphthalene) to as low as 0.03
ppb for higher-molecular-weight PAHs (e.g., pyrene).  SPME with ultraviolet spectroscopy
has also been shown to yield very low detection limits for aromatic pollutants (e.g., low- to
mid-ppb) and has excellent potential for very simple and sensitive field screening methods
using a conventional ultraviolet instrument.  Peer-reviewed publications describing the results
of this investigation are available upon request.<p>
<hr>
<b>Project Manager:</b> Steven B. Hawthorne/<a href=mailto:shawthorne@eerc.und.nodak.edu>shawthorne@eerc.und.nodak.edu </a> <br>
<b>Phone:</b> (701) 777-5256<br>
<b>Informacion en espa&#241;ol:</b> Lucia Romuld/<a href=mailto:lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu>lromuld@eerc.und.nodak.edu</a><br>
<b>Phone:</b> 1-701-777-5223<br>
<b>Sponsor:</b>
<li>U.S. Environmental Protection Agency<br>
<b>Duration of Project:</b>
<li>August 1994 to August 1996<br>
